               <msContents>
                  <summary>F<locus target="#1r"/>-64v: Chants called Mawa'set, specially for use in the funeral, with musical notation. F<locus target="#65rv"/>: Variations of Hallelujah, አንቀጸ፡ ሃሌታ፡. F<locus target="#66r"/>-115r: Chants called Mǝ‘raf, ምዕራፍ፡. Me‘erāf I and II; AṢZ 103–246. <locus target="#115rv"/>: Calculation of the [Favorable} Night, ሐሳበ ሌሊት. <locus target="#78v"/> contains a scribal note of completion and ownership: Here ends Mawa'set, completed on Wednesday in Mäskäräm, the 23rd night and 29th day. In the year of the reign of "እስክንድር" in the year of Luke the Evangelist. This book belongs to የማነ ክርስቶስ, his father ፈታሂ ክርስቶስ, who was the scholar (መምሕረ) of Egora. The scribe is ኢሳይያስ." Illuminations are added recently over text. </summary>
